<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>What time does the US stock market open? (North America)</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">There are several US stock markets, but the most popular are the NYSE and NASDAQ. The New York stock exchange hours are 14:30 to 21:00 UK time (GMT). The NASDAQ trading hours are also 14:30-21:00 UK time.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Nasdaq opening time at 14:30 UK time is essential and we tend to see the highest volume at that time. The Nasdaq is also known as the tech index, because of the sheer number of companies involved in the tech space that are listed on the index. This is where big companies like Apple, Alphabet, Amazon, Tesla and Microsoft are all listed. Foreign companies are also listed on these markets as American Depository Receipts (ADR).</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">
<h3>What time does the stock market open in Canada?</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Toronto Stock Exchange, TSX, opens for trading at 14:30 UK time. The trading session ends at -21:00 GMT. The Toronto Stock Exchange (TSX) is located in Toronto, Canada and is one of the top 10 largest exchanges in the world.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Owned and operated by the TMX Group, it features 1,569 assets which also include ETFs and other derivatives. Among the top 10 stocks on the TSX by market cap are Royal Bank of Canada, Toronto Dominion Bank, Enbridge Inc, Ban of Nova Scotia and Canada National Railway Co. Others are Brookfield Asset Management, Suncor Energy Inc and TransCanada Corp.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">
<h3>What time does the stock market open in Brazil? (South America)</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Ibovespa’s trading hours are 12:00 to 21:00 London time. The Bovespa index, also known as Índice Bovespa or Ibovespa, is Brazil&#8217;s stock exchange. It tracks the performance of 60 stocks traded on the Bolsa Balcão, which is where most of the trading on the Brazilian stock market takes place.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Among the most capitalised stocks on the Ibovespa include Petrobras, Itaú Unibanco, Banco Bradesco, AmBev, Vale, Santander Brasil and Banco do Brasil. Itausa and Telefônica Brasil also make the list.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">
<h3>What time does the stock market open in Mexico? (Latin America)</h3>
<p>The Mexico stock exchange opens at 14:30 UK time and closes at 21:00. Also known as the Mexican Bolsa or Mexbol, the Mexican Stock Exchange is the second-largest stock exchange in Latin America. Owned by the BMV Group, the top-ranked stocks on the exchange by market cap are America Movil, Wal-Mart de Mexico, Southern Copper Corporation, Fomento Economico Mexicano, Grup Mexico, Grupo Elektra, Arca Continental and Grup Financiero Banorte.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" style="width: 1400px;" src="https://www.atfx.com/hubfs/ATFX.COM/NEW%20pages/Pages%20-%20go%20live%20-%20Analysis/Analysis%20-%20C%20-%20Market%20news/Stock%20markets%20opening%20times/analysis-market-news-america-timezone.jpg" alt="analysis-market-news-america-timezone" width="1400" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Stock exchange trading hours in Asia</h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Tokyo stock exchange is Asia’s biggest stock market by market capitalisation, and it’s open between 09:00 to 15:00 local time. However, if you’re based in the UK, the stock market opens at midnight, and closes at six am in the morning. The night hours trading is excellent if trading during the day is not possible for you.</p>
