<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>What time does the stock market open in Japan?</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Tokyo stock exchange opens at 00:00 GMT and closes at 06:00 GMT. The Tokyo Stock exchange is the Nikkei, which tracks the performance of the top 225 stocks in the exchange. Chugai Pharmaceutical, Fast Retailing, Daikin Industries, Daiichi Sankyo and FANUC make up the top five stocks on the Nikkei 225 by market capitalisation.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The price-weighting method has been used to calculate the daily value of the index since 1950, and this is performed annually by the Nihon Keizai Shimbun (The Nikkei) newspaper.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">
<h3>What time does the stock market open in Shanghai, China?</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Shanghai Composite Index (SSE Index) tracks the performance of stocks that trade on both the Shanghai Stock Exchange and a smaller exchange in Shenzhen. It is the 4th largest stock exchange in the world by market capitalization.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The SSE opens at 01:30 GMT and trades till 03:30 GMT, before proceeding on a 90-minute break period. Trading then resumes at 05:00 and closes at 07:00 GMT. Stock trading is composed of the A shares and B shares and commenced in 1991 with a base value of CNY100.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">It tracks the performance of the top 30 companies in Singapore by market capitalisation on the SGX Main Board. DBS Group Holdings makes up 15% of the market cap of the STI, followed by Oversea-Chinese Banking (12.66%) and United Overseas Bank (10.64%). The largest companies by market cap are led by PetroChina, followed by Industrial and Commercial Bank of China, Agricultural Bank of China and Bank of China.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">
<h3><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">What time does the stock market open in Hong Kong?</span></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Hong Kong Stock Exchange opens at 01:30 and closes early in the UK morning at 08:10. The Hang Seng Index tracks the performance of the top 50 companies by market capitalisation on the Hong Kong exchange.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">However, these companies make up only 58% of the exchange&#8217;s total market cap. It was formed 50 years ago. The top companies by market cap include Tencent, followed by Industrial and Commercial Bank of China, Ping An Insurance and China Construction Bank. China Mobile, AIA Group and HSBC are also found in the top 10 companies by market cap on the Hang Seng.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">
<h3><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">What time does the stock market open in South Korea?</span></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The stock market of South Korea is the KOSPI. KOSPI is the acronym for the Korea Composite Stock Price Index and it tracks the performance of 200 common stocks of the Korea Exchange. It started in 1983 with a base value of 100 Won, and is equivalent to the S&amp;P 500 in the US.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The KOSPI’s trading hours start from midnight GMT and end at 06:30 GMT. Samsung Electronics has the largest weighting on the KOSPI, comprising almost 30% of the weight of the KOSPI 200. POSCO, KT, Pan Ocean and Hyundai Motors make up the rest of the top five stocks on the KOSPI by market cap.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">
<h3 style="text-align: justify;"><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">What time does the stock market open in Singapore?</span></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The stock market of the Singapore Exchange, the Straits Times Index (STI) opens at 00:30 GMT and closes at 09:06 GMT. The Straits Times Index is owned by the FTSE Group and the Singapore Exchange (SGX).</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Straits Times Index (STI) dates back to 1966 but has been recalculated several times in its history. The STI tracks the performance of the top 30 companies in Singapore by market capitalisation on the SGX Main Board. DBS Group Holdings makes up 15% of the market cap of the STI, followed by Oversea-Chinese Banking (12.66%) and United Overseas Bank (10.64%).</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img decoding="async" style="width: 1400px;" src="https://www.atfx.com/hubfs/ATFX.COM/NEW%20pages/Pages%20-%20go%20live%20-%20Analysis/Analysis%20-%20C%20-%20Market%20news/Stock%20markets%20opening%20times/analysis-market-news-asia-timezone.jpg" alt="analysis-market-news-asia-timezone" width="1400" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Stock exchange trading hours in the Middle East and Africa</h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This section is made up of the top exchanges in the MENA region (the Middle East and North Africa) as well as the stock exchanges within the African continent. Here, the stock exchanges in Saudi Arabia, Dubai, South Africa, Egypt and Nigeria are featured.</p>
